{{notability|date=January 2017}}
{{primary sources|date=October 2016}}
'''Preminder Singh Sandhawalia''' is a [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] author. 

His first book, published in 1999, was ''Noblemen and Kinsmen History of a Sikh Family''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2000/20001210/spectrum/books.htm#1 |title=Book review on '&#39;Noblemen and Kinsmen: History of a Sikh Family'&#39; |publisher=Tribuneindia.com |date= |accessdate=2012-10-12}}</ref>  His second book ''Beyond Identity'' was released in 2007, and is about his people. It attempts to describe a new path that the Sikh community should follow in the years to be a model people.<ref name="beyond-identity1">[http://www.beyond-identity.org/authorinfo.html Author info]{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} at Sandhawalia's website</ref> Preminder Singh Sandhawalia’s third book, ''CELEBRITY: Its Changing Face in India Through the Ages'' was published in May 2012, and it examines the idea of celebrity in Indian culture through the ages. Sandhawalia explores why celebrity, an honour once accorded to those who performed great feats or provided great service, is now given to entertainers, and hopes his book will encourage readers to “… move away from being mere spectators who indolently look to entertainers to amuse them and return to appreciation of meritocracy and morality.”<ref>{{cite web|last=Singh |first=Preminder |url=http://www.authorhouse.co.uk/Bookstore/BookDetail.aspx?BookId=SKU-000567513 |title=Book Details |publisher=Authorhouse.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2012-10-12}}</ref>

==Books==
* Preminder Singh Sandhawalia (1997) Noblemen and Kinsmen: History of a Sikh Family, Munshiram Manoharlal Publisher, {{ISBN|81-215-0914-9}}
* Preminder Singh Sandhawalia, (2007) Beyond Identity, Singh Brothers, {{ISBN|978-8172053956}}
* Preminder Singh Sandhawalia, (2012), Celebrity: its Changing Face in India Through the Ages, AuthorHouse UK, {{ISBN|978-1468577686}}

