{{inline|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox language |name = Sistani |nativename=سیستونی Sistoni |states = [[Iran]], [[Afghanistan]], [[Tajikistan]],{{cn|date=November 2015}} [[Pakistan]],{{cn|date=November 2015}} [[Turkmenistan]] |speakers=? |ethnicity = Persian [[Sistani Persian people|Sistani]] |familycolor = Indo-European |fam2 = [[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3 = [[Iranian languages|Iranian]] |fam4 = [[Western Iranian languages|Western Iranian]] |fam5 = [[Southwestern Iranian languages|Southwestern]] |fam6 = [[Persian language|Persian]] |iso3 = none |glotto = none }}
'''Sistani''' (also known as ''Sistanian'') is a [[dialect continuum]] spoken by [[Sistani Persian people|Sistani people]] mainly in [[Iran]], [[Afghanistan]], [[Tajikistan]],{{cn|date=November 2015}} [[Pakistan]]{{cn|date=November 2015}} and [[Turkmenistan]]. It is part of the Southwestern [[Iranian languages|Iranian branch]] of the Indo-Iranian group of [[Indo-European languages]], and generally considered a dialect of Persian.
