'''Talking shit (e.g. [[General Grievous]])''' is a term and type of [[trash-talk]] that refers to various types of derogatory language<ref name="Betches 2013 p. 23"/> aimed at an individual or any type of entity, such as a group or organization. Talking shit can be used as a tactic in fighting or brawling, used to draw attention to the matter among onlookers.<ref name="Ferrell Hayward Morrison Presdee 2004"/> This is a term that has been coined more recently and is used in reference when someone talks negatively or spreads false ideas about another person, concept, organization, or entity.

[[Shitposting]] is the act of posting "content of [[Aggression|aggressively]], [[Irony|ironically]], and [[Internet troll|trollishly]] poor quality"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/unclick/simpsons-shitposting-memes-macedonian-clickbait-takeover/|title=How spammers nearly destroyed the biggest 'Simpsons' meme page|last=|first=|date=2016-08-24|website=[[The Daily Dot]]|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> to an [[Internet forum|online forum]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/gadgets-and-tech/news/what-is-shitposting-donald-trump-us-election-2016-palmer-luckey-a7326111.html|title=Shitposting: What is the bizarre online behaviour that could win Donald Trump the election?|last=|first=|date=2016-09-23|website=[[The Independent]]|publisher=|language=en-GB|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/layer8/trumpese-the-donald-glossary-donald-trump/|title=How to speak like a Donald Trump supporter|last=|first=|date=2016-05-02|website=[[The Daily Dot]]|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mic.com/articles/152690/leslie-jones-hack-the-alt-rights-racist-celebration-of-jones-abject-humiliation|title=The racist, sexist alt-right is celebrating over Leslie Jones' abject humiliation|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Mic (media company)]]|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cherwell.org/2016/04/05/purges-and-politics-in-cyberspace/|title=Purges and politics in cyberspace|last=Walker|first=Alex|date=2016-04-05|website=[[Cherwell (newspaper)]]|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.geek.com/news/shitpostbot-5000-proves-internet-memes-will-outlive-humans-1660503/|title=Shitpostbot 5000 proves internet memes will outlive humans|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Geek.com]]|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.papermag.com/multimedia-artist-manuel-arturo-abreu-on-shitposting-and-the-infinite--1986552460.html|title=Multimedia Artist manuel arturo abreu on Shitposting and the Infinite Scroll|last=|first=|date=2016-08-25|website=[[Paper (magazine)]]|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/09/23/papa-whats-a-shitpost/|title=Papa, what's a shitpost?|last=Biggs|first=John|date=2016-09-23|website=[[TechCrunch]]|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://virgula.uol.com.br/comportamento/tentamos-entender-a-obsessao-da-internet-com-memes-da-turma-da-monica/|title=Tentamos entender a obsessão da internet com memes da Turma da Mônica|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Universo Online]] Virgula|publisher=|language=[[Portuguese language]]|trans-title=We try to understand the obsession with internet Monica memes|access-date=}}</ref>

